SALMONELLOSIS, SEROTYPE TYPHIMURIUM - UNITED KINGDOM: PEANUT BUTTER, RECALL
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>


Date: Wed 21 Jan 2009
Source: UK Food Standards Agency [edited]
<http://www.food.gov.uk/enforcement/alerts/2009/jan/larabarsnackbars>


Larabar recalls certain batches of their own brand peanut butter snack bars
Wednesday 21 January 2009

Food Alert: for Information

Ref: 02/2009

Larabar has recalled certain batch and date codes of their own brand
Peanut Butter Cookie flavoured snack bar (51g) and Peanut Butter
Cookie flavoured mini snack bar (21g), due to the possible presence of
Salmonella Typhimurium.

Larabar has withdrawn the affected products from sale and will be
issuing a product recall notice in the national press as of today,
Wednesday 21 January 2009. These notices will alert consumers to the
recall and advise them of what actions to take if they have purchased
the affected products.

The products recalled are:

Batch code Best before
Larabar Peanut Butter Cookie flavour snack bars (51g) 0807021 30 June 2009
Larabar Peanut Butter 0806202 May 2009
Cookie flavour mini snack bars (28g Sample size) FL 11 November 2009

A copy of the text of the product recall notice issued by Larabar can
be found below.

A customer helpline has been provided, the number for which is
0800 0232951 .

No other Larabar products or flavours are known to be affected.

Text of the recall notice issued by Larabar
-------------------------------------------
Larabar peanut butter snack bars

Larabar is voluntarily recalling a limited number of Peanut Butter
Cookie flavour Snack Bars.

Larabar is issuing the recall notice as a precautionary measure after
learning that the peanut butter in these products may be contaminated
with salmonella although no illnesses have been reported in connection
with Larabar products.

Larabar Peanut Butter Cookie flavour snack bars are distributed
nationally and sold primarily as individual bars in grocery and
specialty retail stores in a (51g) bar. However it is also available
in a (28g) sample size bar.

The potentially affected products are listed below:

Batch code Best before
Larabar Peanut Butter Cookie flavour snack bars (51g) 0807021 30 June 2009
Larabar Peanut Butter 0806202 May 2009
Cookie flavour mini snack bars (28g Sample size) FL 11 November 2009

No other flavours of Larabar products are being recalled.

Customers are asked to return the product to the store where they
purchased it. They will receive a full cash refund.

If you prefer you can return the empty packaging to the following
address for a full refund.

Larabar
PO Box 363
Uxbridge
Middlesex
UB8 1YT

You can also speak to us if you would like any further information or
have concerns. The free phone number is: 0800 0232951.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Susan Baekeland

[In the USA, s of 9PM EDT, Sunday, January 25, 2009, 501 persons
infected with the outbreak strain of Salmonella Typhimurium have been
reported from 43 states, plus one from Canada. Among persons with
available information, 22% reported being hospitalized. Infection may
have contributed to 8 deaths. See:
<http://www.cdc.gov/salmonella/typhimurium>. - Mod.JW.]
